{"type":"message","id":"627309cf","parentId":"ad87b34f","timestamp":"2026-03-18T12:44:50.527Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — **as long as you don’t close the one that’s actually running the Gateway process.**\n\nRight now the Gateway is supposed to be running **as a Scheduled Task (SYSTEM)** in the background, so there *shouldn’t* need to be a visible `gateway.cmd` window at all.\n\nHere’s the safe way to tell:\n\n1) Run this:\n- `clawdbot gateway status`\n\nIf it shows **Runtime: running**, then:\n- you can close any random `gateway.cmd`/terminal window you opened manually and **I’ll stay up**.\n\n2) If you *do* have a black `gateway.cmd` window open:\n- If you started it manually by double-clicking or running `gateway.cmd` in a console, closing that window **will stop that manual instance**.\n- But it **won’t** stop the Scheduled Task instance (the one we want), *if that one is actually running*.\n\nIf you want, tell me what `clawdbot gateway status` says (running vs stopped) and I’ll confirm 100% before you close anything.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069ba9e3c3b1c819aa8eecaf2c2e5494c"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":4309,"output":230,"cacheRead":52992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57531,"cost":{"input":0.00754075,"output":0.0032199999999999998,"cacheRead":0.0092736,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02003435}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773837879696}}
