{"type":"message","id":"1e7b415d","parentId":"774081b2","timestamp":"2026-03-18T12:49:13.567Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clawdbot and OpenClaw are related, but they’re not the same thing:\n\n## Clawdbot\n- The **product/runtime you’re running** on your PC.\n- Includes the **Gateway service**, the **CLI (`clawdbot ...`)**, channel connectors (Telegram/etc), skills, scheduling (heartbeat/cron), logs, config, security/auditing—basically the whole “assistant platform.”\n- Think: **the engine + wiring + ops tooling**.\n\n## OpenClaw\n- The **open-source “core” / framework layer** that Clawdbot is built around (or aligned with, depending on version).\n- Think: **the base project/spec that can be self-hosted/extended** without the full “batteries-included” Clawdbot packaging.\n\n## Practical difference for you\n- If you’re asking “what am I actually using day-to-day?” → **Clawdbot**.\n- If you’re asking “what’s the underlying open project / codebase / core architecture?” → **OpenClaw**.\n\nIf you tell me where you saw “OpenClaw” (a GitHub repo link? a config field? a docs page?), I can map it precisely to *your* setup/version and explain what parts you have installed.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069ba9f407214819a995382c73daeb032"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":3365,"output":272,"cacheRead":57472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61109,"cost":{"input":0.00588875,"output":0.0038079999999999998,"cacheRead":0.0100576,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01975435}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773838145092}}
