{"type":"message","id":"cff05955","parentId":"dae2cd7c","timestamp":"2026-03-18T12:50:15.141Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That’s (mostly) a naming/rebrand + “core vs distro” confusion that search results amplify.\n\nWhat’s going on:\n\n- **Clawdbot** = the packaged assistant you’re running (CLI is still `clawdbot`, gateway task is “Clawdbot Gateway”, docs live at `docs.clawd.bot`, etc.).\n- **OpenClaw** = the “open” project name some posts/docs use for the underlying framework/community edition. A lot of people shorthand it as “Clawdbot is now OpenClaw” even when the *runtime/installer/CLI* name hasn’t changed for end users.\n\nSo when Google says “now called OpenClaw”, read it as:\n- “the open-source project / core got branded as OpenClaw”\nnot necessarily\n- “your installed tool renamed and you should stop using `clawdbot`”.\n\nOn your machine right now, you’re definitively on **Clawdbot**:\n- `clawdbot gateway --help` reports **Clawdbot 2026.1.24-3**\n- your service is **Scheduled Task: Clawdbot Gateway**\n- config path is `C:\\Users\\Scott-Pc\\.clawdbot\\clawdbot.json`\n\nIf you want, paste me one of the links you’re seeing and I’ll tell you exactly whether it’s talking about (a) the open core project name, (b) a repo rename, or (c) a migration you actually need to do.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069ba9f7c927c819a8796d88417862bc9"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":238,"output":320,"cacheRead":61056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61614,"cost":{"input":0.0004165,"output":0.00448,"cacheRead":0.0106848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0155813}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773838205169}}
