{"type":"message","id":"db09f438","parentId":"ea0c922c","timestamp":"2026-03-18T12:56:32.491Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it — and I can confirm something important from the live tab:\n\n### What I’m seeing right now\nWhen I click the big **“Shop Tires”** button on the home page, it takes me to:\n\n`/tires/v/2012-chevrolet-malibu?year=2012&make=Chevrolet&model=Malibu&trim=2.4i&modification=...`\n\nSo on *this* tab/session it is **not** dumping me into package results. It’s going to a tires URL.\n\nHowever, the tires page I landed on says:\n> “Select your vehicle in the header to see tires.”\n\nWhich suggests the tires route is loading, but the page is sometimes treating the vehicle context inconsistently (header “garage” selection vs URL params vs cookies). That inconsistency could be what’s flipping you into “packages” in your other flow.\n\n### Next step (to catch the bug)\nCan you do one run where it misroutes, and paste the URL you end up on when it shows “package results”? Even just the path is enough:\n- `/wheels...`\n- `/packages...`\n- `/quote...`\n- or `/tires...` with extra params like `wheelSku` etc.\n\nIf you want, I can also drive the tab and deliberately click through the YMM/trim flow to see if/when it switches.\n\n### Mega menu: yes, let’s simplify it\nI agree with your plan. I’d replace it with a simple header like:\n\n- **Tires** → `/tires` (or your canonical tires landing)\n- **Wheels** → `/wheels`\n- **Schedule** → `/schedule`\n- **Guides** (dropdown) →\n  - Tire size guide\n  - All-season vs winter\n  - TPMS / installation info\n  - FAQ\n- **Contact** → call + location\n\nOnce we confirm the correct tires-only canonical route (so it never falls into packages), we can safely wire all “Tires” entry points to that and kill the mega menu without breaking anything.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa0f6d70c819a848b2e6c6380abb1"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":