{"type":"message","id":"dc02f668","parentId":"b1464273","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:07:57.577Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yep — I can reproduce what you’re describing from that exact URL.\n\nThat URL is landing on the **vehicle-specific tires page**, but it’s effectively behaving like the site only has a tiny subset of SKUs wired up (or it’s applying an implicit constraint that collapses the result set).\n\nA few concrete things I notice from the page content I can see:\n\n- The filters sidebar shows a bunch of placeholders like **“No brand data yet”**, **“Coming soon”**, etc.\n- The page itself even has dev-ish notes like **“Next: wire supplier feed + real filters…”**\n- On the earlier snapshot, the “results” area only had **one** product card (the Nitto Motivo 365), which matches what you’re seeing.\n\nSo this is **not a menu problem**. It’s almost certainly one of these backend/data issues:\n\n### Most likely causes\n1) **Only one supplier feed is currently connected** (or only one SKU is marked active/in-stock), so the API returns 1 tire.\n2) The API has many tires, but the site is filtering them out due to:\n   - missing/incorrect fitment mapping for that trim/modification\n   - a default “in stock near you” filter\n   - a pricing/visibility flag (e.g., MAP, publish=false, inventory=0)\n3) The page route `/tires/v/...` is using a *different* query/service than whatever you’re looking at when you say “128 tires exist” (e.g., the admin/feed has 128, but the shop endpoint only exposes 1).\n\n### Quick way to pinpoint it (fastest next step)\nIf you can tell me where you see “128 tires” (admin panel? supplier portal? a different page/search?), I can identify the mismatch.\n\nEven better: I can hit your warmup endpoint / API endpoints locally and see what `/api/...` returns for that vehicle, but I need to know which endpoint you’re using to view the 128 count (or you can paste a screenshot / link).\n\n### About the mega menu\nYou’re right to want to remove/simplify it, but **it’s not causing the 1-tire issue**. The page you’re landing on is the right one — it’s just under-populated.\n\nTell me: where are you seeing the “128 tires” number (what system/page), and I’ll trace exactly why the storefront route is only rendering 1.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa39e2378819a9991a2c6d8c5b998"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":72081,"output":509,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72590,"cost":{"input":0.12614175,"output":0.0071259999999999995,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.13326775}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773839258374}}
