{"type":"message","id":"487a16c6","parentId":"df3f3264","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:10:22.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect — that explains the “why” pretty cleanly.\n\n### 1) Why the big “Shop Tires” button sent you to `/wheels?...`\nIf your big button is taking you to:\n\n`https://shop.warehousetiredirect.com/wheels?year=2012&make=Chevrolet&model=Malibu&trim=2.4i&modification=...`\n\nthat’s simply **a wrong link target** (or a stateful redirect) on the homepage CTA. It’s not a “tire data” issue — it’s navigation wiring.\n\nOn my side, the homepage “Shop Tires” link *currently* points to `/tires` in the markup, but if you’re being redirected to `/wheels?...` after clicking it, that’s likely one of:\n- the button is sometimes rendered/overwritten by JS with a wheels URL when vehicle context is present\n- or there’s a redirect rule like “if vehicle selected → go to wheels package builder first”\n\nEither way: **we should make Tires always go to tires-only** and Wheels always go to wheels.\n\n### 2) The “128 tires in TireConnect (KM only) but only 1 tire on Warehouse Tire site”\nThat strongly suggests the storefront currently has **wheels feed wired (it’s showing tons: I can see “Total SKUs: 254” on the wheels page)** but the **tires feed is not fully wired/published/mapped** yet — which matches the “No brand data yet / coming soon” placeholders we saw on the tires page.\n\nSo you’re not crazy: the supplier/catalog has the tires, but the shop’s tires pipeline is only exposing a tiny subset.\n\n### 3) I can’t see your TireConnect tab yet\nRight now, Relay is only giving me *one* attached tab (the Warehouse Tire tab). I don’t see a “Warehouse Tire – pontiac” or TireConnect tab in the attached list.\n\nIf you want me to compare side-by-side, you need to:\n- go to the TireConnect / “pontiac” tab\n- click the Relay icon there too (turn it ON for that tab)\n\nThen I’ll be able to read the exact counts/filters and we can map “KM tireconnect results” → “what the shop API returns”.\n\n### Next steps (quick + actionable)\n1) **Attach the TireConnect/Pontiac tab** via Relay so I can see the “128” result context.\n2) Tell me where you want Tires to land:\n   - `/tires` (tires landing)\n   - or directly to the vehicle tires URL `/tires/v/...`\n3) Then we’ll fix nav IA:\n   - Home “Shop Tires” CTA should never point to `/wheels`\n   - Header “TIRES” should be a simple link (no mega menu), plus optional “Guides” dropdown like you suggested.\n\nIf you attach that second tab, I’ll tell you exactly what TireConnect is returning (filters, size, fitment) so we can pinpoint what’s missing in the Warehouse Tire tire feed/mapping.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa42f9010819a88fa230613fbe33f"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":7192,"output":644,"cacheRead":73344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81180,"cost":{"input":0.012586,"output":0.009016,"cacheRead":0.0128352,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0344372}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773839407637}}
