{"type":"message","id":"809237d7","parentId":"6360b1ba","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:19:58.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yep — this works in the managed browser, and it confirms your numbers exactly.\n\nHere’s what I just did in the **managed (clawd) window** on TireConnect:\n\n1) Opened your link and ran the search for raw size **2155517** (location **24407**).\n2) Results came back: **Found 196 tires** (all sources).\n3) Clicked **Inventory** → selected **K&M**.\n4) After filtering to K&M only, it now shows:\n\n- **Found 128 tires for: 2155517**\n- Inventory filter shows **“K&M”** selected.\n\nSo your expectation (“there should be ~128 KM tires”) is correct.\n\n### What this tells us about your shop site problem\nYour WarehouseTire storefront showing **1 tire** for the same vehicle/size is almost certainly because the **KM tire feed isn’t being surfaced/mapped into the storefront tires endpoint**, even though TireConnect can see it.\n\nIn other words:\n- **Wheels feed looks wired (tons of wheel SKUs show up)**\n- **Tires feed is either not wired, not published, or being filtered down hard** (visibility, inventory, pricing, fitment mapping, etc.)\n\n### Next step (pick one)\nIf you tell me how your shop pulls tires (does it call TireConnect directly, or do you import KM into your own DB?), I can help you trace the exact missing link.\n\nTwo quick diagnostics that usually settle it fast:\n1) On the WarehouseTire tires page, is there any “Inventory source / supplier” setting (KM) in admin/config?\n2) If you have an API endpoint on your shop like `/api/tires?...`, we can hit it with the same size and see what count it returns vs TireConnect’s 128.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa6726d30819abda03a499eeb903c"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":1571,"output":377,"cacheRead":104576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106524,"cost":{"input":0.00274925,"output":0.005278,"cacheRead":0.