{"type":"message","id":"33b1483a","parentId":"baea904f","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:22:01.769Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’re using the **KM Tire API directly**, then the “1 tire vs 128 tires” gap is almost certainly happening **in our integration layer** (request params, mapping, filtering, pagination, or response handling) — not in TireConnect.\n\nWe just verified in the managed browser that for **raw size 2155517 @ location 24407**:\n- **All sources:** 196 tires\n- **K&M only:** **128 tires**\n\nSo to pinpoint why your storefront shows only 1, I need 2 things:\n\n1) **Which KM endpoint are we calling for tires** (URL path), and an example request we’re making for that Malibu page.\n   - If you paste a snippet from your code (fetch URL + query/body), that’s enough.\n\n2) **Are we calling it by vehicle (YMMT/modification) or by size?**\n   - TireConnect/KM clearly supports size queries. Your storefront URL is vehicle-based; if we’re converting vehicle→sizes and only picking *one* size (or one axle), you’ll only ever see a tiny subset.\n\nCommon integration mistakes that produce “only 1”:\n- Only requesting **one OEM size** (e.g., only the first chip like 215/55R17) or only **front axle**\n- Hard-coding `limit=1` / only reading the first page / ignoring pagination cursors\n- Filtering out anything with `quantity < 4` (or similar) so almost everything disappears\n- Using the wrong location/warehouse parameter (returns near-empty availability)\n- Treating KM’s “packages” endpoint as “tires” or vice versa\n\nIf you tell me where the KM API code lives in your repo/workspace (file path), I can open it here and we’ll trace the exact request/response path and fix the count.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa6ef52d0819a8eb77873a99fc5f1"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":129,"output":384,"cacheRead":109312,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109825,"cost":{"input":0.000225749999999