{"type":"message","id":"867000b1","parentId":"1d198026","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:31:33.268Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_hLVGazb6i8m9lTpcmNe94nPv|fc_08e128b880ff85f90069baa93076f8819a94c34875d71ecb49","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  const url = new URL(req.url);\n  const base = process.env.PACKAGE_ENGINE_URL;\n  if (!base) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ error: \"Missing PACKAGE_ENGINE_URL\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n\n  const upstream = new URL(\"/v1/vehicles/search\", base);\n  url.searchParams.forEach((v, k) => {\n    // FitmentSelector may store a composite modification value to keep trim options unique.\n    if (k === \"modification\" && typeof v === \"string\" && v.includes(\"__\")) {\n      upstream.searchParams.set(k, v.split(\"__\")[0]);\n      return;\n    }\n    upstream.searchParams.set(k, v);\n  });\n\n  const res = await fetch(upstream, { cache: \"no-store\" });\n  const text = await res.text();\n  return new NextResponse(text, {\n    status: res.status,\n    headers: {\n      \"content-type\": res.headers.get(\"content-type\") || \"application/json\",\n    },\n  });\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773840693260}}
{"type":"message","id":"3329c01b","parentId":"867000b1","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:31:47.241Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — that gives us a clean picture. You’ve got **two systems** in play:\n\n1) **warehouse-tire-site (Vercel / Next.js)**  \n2) **wtd-package-engine (Railway)** at `https://wtd-package-engine-production.up.railway.app/`\n\n### What I found in `warehouse-tire-site`\n#### A) It *does* have a KM endpoint, and it uses your Vercel env key\n`src/app/api/km/tiresizesearch/route.ts` posts to:\n\n- `https://api.kmtire.com/v1/tiresizesearch`\n\n…and reads the key from (any of):\n- `KM_API_KEY` (preferred)\n- `KMTIRE_API_KEY`\n- `KM_TIRE_API_KEY`\n\nSo “api key set in Vercel” is relevant here.\n\n#### B) Your tires page is currently *hard-filtering* KM results to **minQty=4**\nIn `src/app/tires/page.tsx` the KM fetch is:\n\n```ts\nfetch(`${baseUrl}/api/km/tiresizesearch?...&minQty=4`)\n```\n\nThat is a huge reason you can see “only 1 tire” even when TireConnect shows 128.\n\nBecause TireConnect was using **min_quantity=1**, and *you confirmed* the count you want is with **minQty=1**.\n\nSo: **the fastest likely fix** for the “1 tire” problem is simply:\n- change `minQty=4` → `minQty=1` (or make it configurable / user-selectable)\n\nEven better pattern:\n- default to `minQty=1` for browsing\n- only enforce `4` when they add to cart / schedule, or show a “Limited stock” badge when qty < 4.\n\n### What I found about the Railway package engine URL\nYour Next.js vehicle/fitment routes proxy to the package engine using:\n\n- `process.env.PACKAGE_ENGINE_URL`\n\nExample: `src/app/api/vehicles/search/route.ts` calls:\n- `GET <PACKAGE_ENGINE_URL>/v1/vehicles/search?...`\n\nSo: **Vercel needs `PACKAGE_ENGINE_URL=https://wtd-package-engine-production.up.railway.app/`** (or whatever your real base is).\n\nAlso FYI: `https://wtd-package-engine-production.up.railway.app/` returns **Cannot GET /** (404), which is normal if the API only serves `/v1/...` routes.\n\n---\n\n## What I need from you to finish this cleanly\n1) Do you want the storefront to show tires that have **at least 1 in stock** (minQty=1) or **at least 4** (minQty=4) by default?\n   - Based on your TireConnect comparison, sounds like **minQty=1**.\n\nIf you confirm “minQty=1”, I can make the code change in `warehouse-tire-site` and you can deploy it to Vercel.\n\n2) (Optional but important) On Vercel, confirm these env vars in **Production**:\n- `KM_API_KEY` (or whichever name you used)\n- `PACKAGE_ENGINE_URL = https://wtd-package-engine-production.up.railway.app/`\n\nIf you tell me the exact env var names you set in Vercel right now, I’ll make sure they match what the code actually reads.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa935459c819aada81ef1cb66817c"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":346,"output":712,"cacheRead":151296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152354,"cost":{"input":0.0006055,"output":0.009968,"cacheRead":0.026476799999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.037050299999999994}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773840693268}}
