{"type":"message","id":"44afd5b9","parentId":"25444924","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:32:12.968Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it: the doc you mentioned is in the workspace root as **`C:\\Users\\Scott-Pc\\clawd\\km tire API Portal.pdf`**.\n\nTwo important notes based on what we already saw in your code:\n\n- Your storefront is calling **`https://api.kmtire.com/v1/tiresizesearch`** (XML POST) via `warehouse-tire-site/src/app/api/km/tiresizesearch/route.ts`.\n- The reason you’re seeing “only 1 tire” on the site is very likely **not the API key**, but the fact that the UI is requesting **`minQty=4`** (while TireConnect showed your 128 count with **minQty=1**).\n\n### Quick question\nDo you want the *default* storefront browse behavior to be **minQty=1** (show everything that exists, even if you can’t fulfill 4 immediately), and then handle qty/availability at checkout/scheduling?\n\nIf you say “yes”, I’ll change `warehouse-tire-site` so the KM call uses `minQty=1` (or makes it a user-selectable filter), and that should make your result counts match your expectations a lot more closely.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa9562dfc819aa510bc60fb663a40"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":21803,"output":254,"cacheRead":152448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":174505,"cost":{"input":0.03815525,"output":0.003556,"cacheRead":0.026678399999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.06838965}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773840724312}}
