{"type":"message","id":"ab2c61ba","parentId":"b22bd802","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:34:58.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That’s a really useful data point.\n\nIt means:\n\n- With **minQty=1**, TireConnect (KM-only) showed **128** tires.\n- With **minQty=4**, TireConnect (KM-only) shows **113** tires.\n\nSo if our KM API integration is using `minQty=4`, the “correct” ballpark for *KM-only* should be **~113**, not 1.\n\nIf you’re still seeing **only 1** tire on the Warehouse Tire site, then we’ve got an additional problem beyond minQty, like:\n\n1) **We’re only querying one tire size** (e.g., only one OEM size / one axle), instead of all applicable sizes.\n2) **We’re filtering further in the UI** after the KM response (brand/season/speed/price filters, or “in stock near you” logic).\n3) **We’re not rendering all returned items** (pagination bug / only taking first item / mapping bug).\n4) **KM API response parsing**: we might be dropping items because fields aren’t where we expect (but our adapter already handles arrays vs single item pretty well).\n\n### Quick test (takes 30 seconds)\nOpen this in your browser (your deployed Vercel site), replacing with your domain if needed:\n\n`/api/km/tiresizesearch?tireSize=215/55R17&minQty=4&debug=1`\n\nWhat I want to know from that JSON response:\n- does it show `items.length` anywhere near **113** (or at least dozens)?\n- or is `items.length` actually 1 (meaning KM upstream is returning only 1 to us)\n\nIf `items.length` is large but the UI shows 1 → it’s a UI/filter/render issue.\nIf `items.length` is 1 → it’s either request params (wrong size being requested) or KM upstream response for that size is truly 1.\n\nIf you paste the first ~30 lines of that JSON (or just tell me `items.length`), I’ll tell you exactly where the remaining loss is happening.","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baa9f41cb0819a8fa5d2c5b6a708cc"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","