":"That JSON you pasted is the smoking gun — and it also explains **exactly** why your storefront is only showing 1 tire.\n\n### What your KM endpoint is returning\nFrom your response:\n\n- `resultCode: \"0\"` (success)\n- `debug.itemCount: 64`\n\nSo **KM is absolutely returning dozens of tires for 2155517** (with minQty=4 *or at least with whatever rule KM applies internally*).\n\nSo the KM API + key are fine.\n\n### Why your *site* still shows only 1 tire\nYour `warehouse-tire-site` tires page is **intentionally ignoring KM results unless WheelPros returns zero**.\n\nIn `warehouse-tire-site/src/app/tires/page.tsx` you currently have:\n\n```ts\nconst itemsKm: Tire[] = Array.isArray(km?.items) ? km.items : [];\nconst itemsWp: Tire[] = Array.isArray(wp?.items) ? wp.items : [];\n\n// IMPORTANT: Tire detail pages (/tires/[sku]) currently read from our wp_tires table.\n// KM-style SKUs may not exist in wp_tires, causing \"Tire not found\" on click.\n// Until we add a unified tire detail resolver, prefer WP-backed items only.\nconst itemsRaw: Tire[] = itemsWp;\n\n// If WP returns nothing, fall back to KM so users still see something.\nconst itemsFallback: Tire[] = itemsRaw.length ? itemsRaw : itemsKm;\n```\n\nSo if WheelPros returns **1** tire for that size, the UI will show **that 1** and completely drop the 64 KM tires on the floor.\n\nThat matches your behavior perfectly.\n\n### What we should do next (your call)\nYou’ve got two options:\n\n**Option A (fastest): show KM tires even when WP returns something**\n- Change the logic to **merge** results (WP + KM), or at least “prefer KM when it has more”.\n- Downside: clicking a KM tire might break if you don’t have a tire detail page that can resolve KM SKUs yet (your comment says that’s why you disabled it).\n\n**Option B (cleanest): add a unified tire detail resolver**\n- Update `/tires/[sku]` to fetch details from WP *or* KM depending on SKU/source.\n- Then you can safely show all KM items and still have working detail