{"type":"message","id":"f69bd833","parentId":"2d572373","timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:46:48.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yep — we set it up like a real “multi-supplier catalog”:\n\n### What I changed (locally, in `warehouse-tire-site`)\n1) **Results page now merges tires from BOTH suppliers**\n- Instead of “prefer WP, only show KM if WP is empty”, the `/tires` page now:\n  - pulls WP results\n  - pulls KM results\n  - **merges them into one list** (keeping a `source: \"wp\" | \"km\"` tag on each item)\n\n2) **KM tires now have a real detail page**\n- New route:  \n  **`/tires/km/[partNumber]`**\n- When you click a KM tire, it opens that detail page (not Schedule).\n\n3) **WP tires still use the existing WP detail page**\n- WP → `/tires/[sku]` (your existing DB-backed page)\n- KM → `/tires/km/[partNumber]` (new page)\n\n### Why this is the scalable model\nWhen you add a 3rd/4th vendor later, you just:\n- add another `fetchVendorXTires()`\n- normalize results to the same shape (`source`, `sku/partNumber`, `brand`, `description`, `cost`, `qty`)\n- merge into the list\n- add a detail route for that vendor (or a unified resolver later)\n\n### Status\n- Build passes (`npm run build` succeeded)\n- Changes are committed:  \n  **`82c7a77 Show tires from WP and KM; add KM tire detail page`**\n\n### Next step\nDo you want me to:\n1) **push this commit** to the repo (so you can deploy on Vercel), or\n2) just tell you exactly which files changed and you’ll deploy manually?\n\nFiles changed:\n- `src/app/tires/page.tsx`\n- `src/app/tires/km/[partNumber]/page.tsx`","textSignature":"msg_08e128b880ff85f90069baacbfb0a4819aa85707aeaafecad5"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":211,"output":404,"cacheRead":197376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":197991,"cost":{"input":0.00036925,"output":0.005656,"cacheRead":0.034540799999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.04056604999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773